Privacy Policy for Ball Sort Puzzle
Last Updated: February 7, 2026
Introduction
Ball Sort Puzzle ("we", "our", or "us") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application Ball Sort Puzzle (the "App").
Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. By using the App, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

1. Information We Collect
1.1 Information You Provide
We may collect the following information that you provide directly:

Game Progress Data: Level completion, scores, stars earned, coins collected
Purchase Information: In-app purchase history (managed by Google Play Store)
Account Information: If you choose to sign in (email address, username)

1.2 Automatically Collected Information
When you use our App, we automatically collect:

Device Information: Device type, operating system version, unique device identifiers
Usage Data: Game sessions, features used, time spent in app, levels played
Performance Data: Crash reports, error logs, app performance metrics
Advertising ID: For personalized advertising (you can opt-out in device settings)

1.3 Information from Third Parties
We work with third-party services that may collect information:

Google Play Services: For app functionality and analytics
Google AdMob: For displaying advertisements
Google Play Billing: For processing in-app purchases


2. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected information for:
2.1 App Functionality

Saving your game progress and settings
Providing game features (hints, undos, coins)
Processing in-app purchases
Restoring purchases across devices

2.2 App Improvement

Analyzing app usage and performance
Identifying and fixing bugs and crashes
Improving game features and user experience
Understanding user preferences

2.3 Advertising

Displaying relevant advertisements
Measuring ad performance
Providing personalized ad experiences (you can opt-out)

2.4 Communication

Sending important app updates
Responding to your support requests
Notifying you about new features


3. Data Storage and Security
3.1 Data Storage

Local Storage: Game progress stored on your device using secure local storage
Cloud Storage: Optional cloud backup via Google Play Games Services
Retention: We retain data only as long as necessary for app functionality

3.2 Security Measures
We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data:

Encrypted data transmission (HTTPS/SSL)
Secure storage on device
Regular security updates
Limited access to personal data

However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure. While we strive to protect your data, we cannot guarantee absolute security.

4. Third-Party Services
Our App uses the following third-party services that may collect data:
4.1 Google Play Services

Purpose: App functionality, analytics, cloud save
Data Collected: Device info, usage data, gameplay data
Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy

4.2 Google AdMob

Purpose: Displaying advertisements
Data Collected: Advertising ID, device info, location (approximate)
Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy
Opt-Out: You can opt-out of personalized ads in your device settings

4.3 Google Play Billing

Purpose: Processing in-app purchases
Data Collected: Purchase history, payment information (handled by Google)
Privacy Policy: https://payments.google.com/payments/apis-secure/get_legal_document?ldo=0&ldt=privacynotice


5. Advertising
5.1 Types of Ads

Banner Ads: Displayed during gameplay
Interstitial Ads: Shown between levels
Rewarded Video Ads: Optional ads for earning coins

5.2 Personalized Advertising

We use Google AdMob which may show personalized ads based on your interests
Ads are based on Advertising ID (not personal information like name or email)
You can opt-out of personalized advertising:

Android: Settings → Google → Ads → Opt out of Ads Personalization
iOS: Settings → Privacy → Advertising → Limit Ad Tracking



5.3 Ad-Free Option
You can remove all advertisements by purchasing the "Remove Ads" feature or VIP subscription.

6. Children's Privacy
6.1 Age Restrictions
Our App is suitable for all ages, including children. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 without parental consent.
6.2 COPPA Compliance
We comply with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA):

No personal information collection from children under 13
No third-party advertising targeted at children
Parental controls available through device settings

6.3 Parental Rights
If you are a parent/guardian and believe your child has provided personal information, please contact us to request deletion.

7. Your Privacy Rights
7.1 Access and Control
You have the right to:

Access: Request a copy of your data
Correction: Request correction of inaccurate data
Deletion: Request deletion of your data
Opt-Out: Opt-out of personalized advertising
Data Portability: Request your data in a portable format

7.2 How to Exercise Your Rights
To exercise these rights:

Delete Data: Uninstall the app (deletes local data)
Opt-Out of Ads: Use device settings (see Section 5.2)
Data Requests: Contact us at [YOUR EMAIL ADDRESS]


8. Data Sharing and Disclosure
8.1 We Do NOT Sell Your Data
We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties.
8.2 We May Share Data With:

Service Providers: Google Play Services, AdMob (for app functionality)
Legal Requirements: If required by law or to protect our rights
Business Transfers: In case of merger, acquisition, or sale of assets

8.3 Anonymous Data
We may share aggregated, anonymous data (not linked to you) for:

Analytics and research
Marketing purposes
Industry reports


9. International Data Transfers
Our App is available globally. Your data may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your own. We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place to protect your data in accordance with this Privacy Policy.

10. Changes to Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be:

Posted in the App
Effective immediately upon posting
Notified through App update notes

Last Updated: February 7, 2026
We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.

