If you are a California resident, you have additional rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA):

Right to know what personal information is collected
Right to delete personal information
Right to opt-out of sale of personal information (we don't sell data)
Right to non-discrimination for exercising your rights

To exercise these rights, contact us at [YOUR EMAIL ADDRESS].

13. European Privacy Rights (GDPR)
If you are in the European Economic Area (EEA), you have rights under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR):

Right to access your data
Right to rectification of inaccurate data
Right to erasure ("right to be forgotten")
Right to restrict processing
Right to data portability
Right to object to processing
Right to withdraw consent

To exercise these rights, contact us at [YOUR EMAIL ADDRESS].
Legal basis for processing:

Consent: You consent by using the App
Legitimate Interest: Improving app performance and user experience
Contractual Necessity: Providing app features and services


14. Data Retention
We retain your data for as long as:

You use the App (game progress, settings)
Required by law (purchase records)
Necessary for legitimate business purposes (analytics, up to 2 years)

When data is no longer needed, we securely delete it.

15. Cookies and Similar Technologies
Our App does not use cookies, but third-party services (Google AdMob) may use similar technologies:

Device Identifiers: For advertising and analytics
Local Storage: For saving game data on device

You can manage these through your device settings.

16. Your Consent
By using Ball Sort Puzzle, you consent to:

This Privacy Policy
Collection and use of information as described
Third-party services (Google Play, AdMob)

If you do not agree, please do not use the App.

17. Disclaimer
While we take reasonable measures to protect your data, we cannot guarantee:

Absolute security (no system is 100% secure)
Prevention of unauthorized access
Protection against all security threats

Use the App at your own risk.

